body:
Yeah, you are right @roji @aleksvujic "null" does render as `JsonTokenType.Null` but we don't have any special processing for it when including json entity.

wrt workaround, projecting JSON entity works just fine (method for materializing Json entity on top level contains the logic that checks for null value), so you could project all the properties of `Product` separately and then stitch them into an entity on the client. But that loses you tracking, so the workaround is not great.

```cs
        var projection = await ctx.Products.AsNoTracking().Select(x => new { x.Id, x.ConfigJSON }).ToListAsync();
        var products = projection.Select(x => new Product { Id = x.Id, ConfigJSON = x.ConfigJSON }).ToList();
```
